  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      the study compares the use of end tidal (Et) control of sevoflurane during anesthesia for
      living donor hepatectomy versus fresh gas (FGF) control. Et control is hypothesized to be as
      effective as FGF control with less cost and more operator satisfaction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
